  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette </strong>into quarters lengthways, then chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720000105018-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720000105018-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720000105018-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720000105018-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720000105018-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required) to a large bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), the <strong>drained lentils</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Divide and shape into meatballs (6 per person!) – these are your <strong>pork & lentil meatballs</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720000174600-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720000174600-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720000174600-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720000174600-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720000174600-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (or two, preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>pork & lentil meatballs</strong> to the pan[s] and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned, then remove to a plate and reserve the pan[s]</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped onion </strong>to the reserved pan[s] over a medium-high heat with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>,<strong> </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften (be careful when adding the water to the pan, it may sizzle from the heat of the oil!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720000179133-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720000179133-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720000179133-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720000179133-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720000179133-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once starting to soften, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>to the pan with your<strong> dried oregano </strong>and<strong> tomato paste </strong>and cook for 30 secs until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> with your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>, a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, then give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the <strong>browned pork & lentil meatballs </strong>to the pan and cook, covered for 12-15 min, or until the sauce has thickened and the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720000183963-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720000183963-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720000183963-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720000183963-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720000183963-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni</strong> for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>wholewheat tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720000188172-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720000188172-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720000188172-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720000188172-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720000188172-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720000202420-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720000202420-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720000202420-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720000202420-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720000202420-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> cooked tortiglioni </strong>to the pan with a splash of<strong> starchy pasta water</strong> and gently stir it all together, being careful not to break up the meatballs</p><p>Cook for a final 1-2 min or until thickened and the sauce is coating the tortiglioni – this is your <strong>pork & lentil meatballs with wholewheat tortiglioni</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720000215630-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720000215630-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720000215630-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720000215630-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720000215630-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> pork & lentil meatballs with wholewheat tortiglioni </strong>with the<strong> salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Top the salad with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the<strong> grated Italian cheese</strong> all over and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
